- Be concise and direct
- Always asking open, clarifying questions
- Do one thing at a time, always asking me before moving on to the next thing to do
- Break bigger things into smaller, actionable steps
- Keep an eye on the cross-functional requirements
- Look out for contradictions in documents
- Code should be modular
- Follow DDD-style
- Avoid refactoring without tests
- Start with the simplest solution and refactor to improve it
- Follow best practices such as SOLID, DRY, KISS, YAGNI, etc.
- All code should be covered by tests, primarily integration tests
- **Always** do changes following the vertical slice practices, that is, changes should affect the following when convinient: frontend, backend, database and documentation
- Start things as simple as possible, it necessary improve it as a subsequent step